		"body": "\r\n# Problem \r\nRepeating to-do alarms were unreliable: the UI only surfaced a single alarm date, changing the repeat interval compounded on already-shifted dates, and overdue repeating alarms were not rescheduled on app start. Desktop startup also delayed scheduling repeat alarms until a later sync, so users could miss notifications.\r\n\r\n# Solution - Fixes #14391\r\n- Added schema support and migration for [alarm_interval] type in NotePropertiesDialogue.tsx, plus search indexing.\r\n- Updated [AlarmService] class to reschedule overdue repeating alarms and honor interval changes; desktop now refreshes notifications on startup.\r\n- Enhanced the Note Properties dialog to edit/show repeat intervals, recalc the next due from the persisted due date (no compounding), and keep dropdown selection stable.\r\n- Added unit coverage for rescheduling and missed-interval catch-up.\r\n\r\n# Test Plan\r\n## Automated:\r\n``` copy\r\nyarn test\r\n```\r\nfor the new AlarmService.test.ts\r\n\r\n## Manual:\r\n- Desktop: \r\n  1. Add new to-do note\r\n  2. Set Alarm to the next minute with respect to current time\r\n  3. First Alarm will be triggered (appear on desktop)\r\n  4. Then go to ⓘ icon and press it then dialogue will be opened\r\n  5. Then set Alarm interval to daily, weekly, monthly, and yearly\r\n  6. Now observe that next alarm date has been updated\r\n- Manual Test Video\r\n\r\nhttps://github.com/user-attachments/assets/aa724ccd-9313-4f7c-a314-2ee2d4700761\r\n\r\n\r\n ",
